{% extends "../partials/layout.njk" %}

{% set title = "Book a secure move" %}

{% block content %}
  <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">{{title}}</h1>

  <p>This service allows you to schedule secure movement for someone in custody between locations across England and Wales.</p>

  <p>This is only for the movement of prisoners using the Prisoner Escort and Custodial Services (PECS) suppliers - these are:</p>

  <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>GEOAmey in Wales and in the north of England</li>
    <li>Serco in the south of England</li>
  </ul>

  <p>The service cannot be used for movements completed by any other escorts except GEOAmey and Serco.</p>

  <p>Once a move has been scheduled, the service provides details to the suppliers and the receiving location of the person being moved.</p>

  <p>The service is also used for the completing a digital Person Escort Record (dPER), which provides relevant details to the escort suppliers and the receiving location. Details can include:</p>

  <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>who is being transported</li>
    <li>any associated risks involving those being transported</li>
    <li>offence information</li>
    <li>the personâ€™s property which is travelling with them</li>
    <li>any relevant health updates</li>
    <li>who is handing over the prisoner and who is receiving them</li>
  </ul>
 
  <p>If you have any problems with this service, contact the helpdesk by calling 0800 917 5148, or #6598 from inside a prison. You can also contact <a href="mailto:bookasecuremove@digital.justice.gov.uk">bookasecuremove@digital.justice.gov.uk</a>.</p>

  <p><a href="https://eu.surveymonkey.com/r/3CKYXSC">You can also provide feedback on the service using the online form.</a></p>
